Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Damascus, 13 Feb (MENA) -- U.S. Ambassador in Syria 
Christopher Ross has stressed his country's seriousness in 
establishing a comprehensive, just peace in the region. He 
said: Let us wait and see the outcome of the Arab-Israeli talks 
in Washington the day after tomorrow, that is, Tuesday. 
  In a statement to the MENA correspondent in Damascus, Ross 
ruled out the possibility of U.S. Secretary of State Warren 
Christopher's touring the region's countries at present. 

